    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 for a Class II device with Medium model influence. Hemolysis index validation error (9.1% NRMSE) is within the 15% acceptance threshold. Geometric tolerance sensitivity sweep confirms RH < 1 across the full tolerance space with 99.7% probability. Uncertainty quantification provided for mesh convergence, pressure-flow validation, and sensitivity analysis. The credibility body of evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory decision that the CFD model can reliably identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB device. Assessment accepted.",
